a) due to me being impatient 
b) due to you being impatient (and reading incorrectly^^)
c) my smartphones fault! 
d) bc englisch is not even my native tongue
Or e) it was simply intended. 
Anyway, nobody even cares what is written beyond the pictures, am I right? 
Is there anyone interested in reading this? Idk. I'm asking u, feel free to comment 😃

If you DO intend and/or are interested in following my future posts be aware of my soliloquies kay? They tend to show from time to time ^^ See u soon 😘

Purifying Palmarosa Skincare Kit 💛

This kit is an introduction to our naturally mattifying Purifying Palmarosa skincare range & is perfect for oily skin types & oily T-zones.
The lush, organic palmarosa grass that is distilled & used in our Purifying Palmarosa range is primarily sourced from plantations in Uganda, as well as from India & Madagascar. Our Ugandan palmarosa is harvested by hand in the fields near the town of Tororo. In a beautiful, compact canvas bag, with a 10-14 day supply, this kit is ideal for travelling & offers a ready to go skincare ritual, with results you’ll love!

What is in me? 💛
- Cleanse; Purifying Palmarosa Facial Wash (25ml) – This gently foaming wash removes impurities for fresh, clean skin.
- Tone; Purifying Palmarosa Toner (25ml) – This refreshing toner helps minimise the appearance of pores.
- Moisturise; Purifying Palmarosa Daily Moisture (15ml) – Enjoy a healthy, matte complexion with this hydrating moisturiser.
- Treatment; Purifying Palmarosa Facial Mask (15g) – Help balance oils & minimise the appearance of blemishes.

We've also popped a sachet of our Purifying Palmarosa Mattifier inside for an extra treat 💛

GOOD TO KNOW 🌱
The lush, wild growing palmarosa grass that we source from Uganda is harvested by hand in the fields near the town of Tororo. The distillation site was created with sustainability in mind & uses solar panels & recycled agricultural waste as source of fuel.

It has been a while and many new followers since I introduced myself! I'm Lauren! I live in Michigan and started this website last November. I had been feeling pretty misunderstood as a highly sensitive person and had been doing tons of research on it. That's when it hit me to create an affordable, easy to understand course for other highly sensitive people to learn to deal with the challenges, get acceptance & learn to embrace their talents and gifts as a HSP! So more about me? I bought a house in March and live with my boyfriend and his two pups (and love it!). My days are filled with freelancing work and spending time with friends & family (while still getting my much needed introvert alone time!). My guilty pleasures (although I don't believe you need to feel guilty for liking anything!) are reality tv, cooking shows, rap music (although pop alternative will always be my fave music) & frozen yogurt. Now is your turn! Comment below and introduce yourself and tell me how I can better support you! 😘👇

Hey guys! So it has occurred to me that I have never really introduced myself to those of you who don't know me and most of you couldn't pick me out of a lineup since it is always just hair pics that I post! Well that's about to change! Most icebreakers will have you say one random fact about yourself but it must be your lucky day...you get 10!
1.) I have been coloring hair for over ten years and am more passionate about my career now than ever before.
2.) I have an obsession with sharpie markers and WILL steal yours if given half the chance. You've been warned.
3.) Sometimes when I'm on the bus my mind wanders to zombie apocalypse survival strategy. I have taken several Facebook quizzes and they all say I'll make it so stick with me!!
4.) I have an adorable cat named Mini and we have a love/hate relationship...I love her, she hates me...most of the time...
5.) I love all things culinary...as is obvious by the pic accompanying this post.
6.) I have dual citizenship with the US and Canada. Thanks Mum! 
7.) I call my mom "mum" because of said Canadian affiliation. Yep, kids thought it was weird growing up. 
8.) I went to beauty school because I thought I wanted to be a makeup artist...I didn't.
9.) One of my favorite things on this planet is a good pair of broken in Converse All-Stars. 
10.) Flamingos and I are not friends. They are pink and they smell.
Thanks for playing guys! I would love to hear something random about you to make me feel better about being such a weirdo! 😂😂😂

Hi 👋I am Jen & I have not posted in a hot minute 😂😂- I am not gonna lie, I have struggled with social media in the aspect of "what am I using this for?" "What are my intentions?"...do I combine my personal life with my business? And if I do, how "raw" do I get? How can I use this platform for some good & not just pretty pics of jewelry and motivational quotes? 🤔 I know this word is overused & dare I say "trendy" , but what I have determined is the best answer is to be AUTHENTIC. To do what I feel without second guessing it. 🙌 going forward I might post pics of my dogs, my husband, the boutiques, colorado landscapes, selfies with my loved ones, a good hair day, my latest handmade jewelry, a bad hair day, a peek into the struggle with my weight/food and how I am losing lbs, our latest project on our fixer upper home, things I am proud of, things I am embarrassed or quite frankly ashamed of ...because that is what makes this life a wild beautiful ride & we are all on it together. 🌎 ✌🏼I am not out for a bigger number of followers but rather  follower-friends that feel my vibe. I hope you love the jewelry I make, the clothing we offer and are able to visit my boutiques in Colorado but most importantly, I hope we get to know eachother- CONNECT and become better people because of it. 💁🏼 PS- this pic was taken a few days ago when I was taking advantage of a good hair day😂...showcasing my bar necklace with my favorite quote of all time "SheWhoDaresWins" 💁🏼#appropriate #HelloAgain #keepinItReal #shewhodareswins #shamelessselfie #authenticity #letsconnect #goodvibes #jewelrydesigner #introduction #reallife #WelcomeToMyNewInstagram #LoveHarper #LoveHarperBoutique #colorado
